:"mentions"},{"source":"recSQPnh6OYztxqL0","target":"rec8hi9Ksp4awz9FJ","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recSQPnh6OYztxqL0","target":"recxiSg5QZWkj9Hy3","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recSQPnh6OYztxqL0","target":"receEjvf5hXhkgVuZ","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recSQPnh6OYztxqL0","target":"rec1RMZhQrrzq5oHJ","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recSQPnh6OYztxqL0","target":"recC23N5Tc2A2DvIi","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recSQPnh6OYztxqL0","target":"recfrXyxhuYOczKTm","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recSQPnh6OYztxqL0","target":"recRxBBePxyyV6TFO","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recSQPnh6OYztxqL0","target":"recIJFRcqI6KbKgXb","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recSQPnh6OYztxqL0","target":"recQ1bj3p4Lj5MYY6","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recgpzXZxax2c3dWn","ref":"Isa.23.1","text":"The burden of Tyre. Howl, ye ships of Tarshish; for it is laid waste, so that there is no house, no entering in: from the land of Chittim it is revealed to them.","year":-715},{"id":"recOe4StpHfY9OiB7","ref":"Isa.23.2","text":"Be still, ye inhabitants of the isle; thou whom the merchants of Zidon, that pass over the sea, have replenished.","year":-715},{"id":"reczTJXyyrkugH16c","ref":"Isa.23.3","text":"And by great waters the seed of Sihor, the harvest of the river, is her revenue; and she is a mart of nations.","year":-715},{"id":"recTC6aFfzUQLHDZL","ref":"Isa.23.4","text":"Be thou ashamed, O Zidon: for the sea hath spoken, even the strength of the sea, saying, I travail not, nor bring forth children, neither do I nourish up young men, nor bring up virgins.","year":-715},{"id":"recm6HbJi0JAbCL8g","ref":"Isa.23.5","text":"As at the report concerning Egypt, so shall they be sorely pained at the report of Tyre.","year":-715},{"id":"recOfoW43yBXvEuIq","ref":"Isa.23.6","text":"Pass ye over to Tarshish; howl, ye inhabitants of the isle.","year":-715},{"id":"recXXH211YQ8zoBVu","ref":"Isa.23.7","text":"Is this your joyous city, whose antiquity is of ancient days? her own feet shall carry her afar off to sojourn.","year":-715},{"id":"recFT3btiLC2afzep","ref":"Isa.23.8","text":"Who hath taken this counsel against Tyre, the crowning city, whose merchants are princes, whose traffickers are the honourable of the earth?","year":-715}]}
